<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Big 12 Releases Women’s Basketball 2026-27 Opponents</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/womens-basketball-big-12-releases-womens-basketball-2026-27-opponents</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/11/womens-basketball-big-12-releases-womens-basketball-2026-27-opponents</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WBB 2026-27 Big 12 Schedule Matrix" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/11/WBB_SCHEDMATRIX_26_1920x1080.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. - The Big 12 announced the conference scheduling matrix for the 2026-27 women's basketball season. Teams will play three Big 12 opponents twice, then play the other 12 conference opponents one time, for a total of 18 conference games.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/WBB_SCHEDMATRIX_26_1920x1080.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/WBB_SCHEDMATRIX_26_1920x1080.png"><media:title>WBB 2026-27 Big 12 Schedule Matrix</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/11/WBB_SCHEDMATRIX_26_1920x1080.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 12:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59183</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Advance to College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The West Virginia Baseball team poses for a photo after winning the NCAA Morgantown Super Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the first time in program history, the West Virginia University baseball team is going to the Men's College World Series after finishing off a two-game sweep of Cal Poly in the NCAA Super Regionals with a 17-1 victory over the Mustangs on Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 45-15 on the season, setting a new program record for wins.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg"><media:title>The West Virginia Baseball team poses for a photo after winning the NCAA Morgantown Super Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 6 Jun 2026 20:49:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59172</s:story_id></item><item><title>Yehl, Kelly, Cole Collect All-America Honors</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/10/baseball-yehl-kelly-cole-collect-all-america-honors</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/10/baseball-yehl-kelly-cole-collect-all-america-honors</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chansen Cole, Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/10/BB26_ColeYehlKelly.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – Three members of the West Virginia University baseball team have picked up All-America honors. Redshirt junior Maxx Yehl was named to the first team by Perfect Game and the second team by NCBWA, sophomore Gavin Kelly earned second-team honors by Perfect Game and NCBWA, and sophomore Chansen Cole was named to the second team by NCBWA.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/BB26_ColeYehlKelly.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/BB26_ColeYehlKelly.jpg"><media:title>Chansen Cole, Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/BB26_ColeYehlKelly.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 13:37:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59182</s:story_id></item><item><title>Four Mountaineers Named ABCA All-East Region</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/9/baseball-four-mountaineers-named-abca-all-east-region</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/9/baseball-four-mountaineers-named-abca-all-east-region</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly, Chansen Cole, and Ian Korn are featured as ABCA All-East Region Selections" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/9/Untitled-1ABCA.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va.  – Four West Virginia University baseball players have been named ABCA All-East Region. Redshirt junior starting pitcher Maxx Yehl was named to the first team while sophomore starting pitcher Chansen Cole, sophomore catcher Gavin Kelly, and graduate relief pitcher Ian Korn earned spots on the second team.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/Untitled-1ABCA.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/Untitled-1ABCA.jpg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly, Chansen Cole, and Ian Korn are featured as ABCA All-East Region Selections</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/Untitled-1ABCA.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 9 Jun 2026 13:04:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59180</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia to Play Troy in First Game of College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-west-virginia-to-play-troy-in-first-game-of-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-west-virginia-to-play-troy-in-first-game-of-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup vs. Troy" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team will play its first game of the Men's College World Series against Troy on Friday, June 12, at 2 p.m. ET. The game will air on ESPN and WVU will be the designated home team.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg"><media:title>Matchup vs. Troy</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 8 Jun 2026 12:21:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59174</s:story_id></item><item><title>Luck’s Vision Becoming a Reality</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-lucks-vision-becoming-a-reality</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-lucks-vision-becoming-a-reality</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia celebrates a run during its 17-1 victory over Cal Poly at Ken Kendrick Family Ballpark on Saturday, June 6, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/8/Baseball-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – When Bridgeport's Ben McDougal registered the final out of West Virginia's Super Regional-clinching 17-1 victory over Cal Poly at Kendrick Family Ballpark on Saturday afternoon, there was one man in Colorado sitting in front of his flat-screen television with a mile-high smile on his face.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/Baseball-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/Baseball-Main.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia celebrates a run during its 17-1 victory over Cal Poly at Ken Kendrick Family Ballpark on Saturday, June 6, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/Baseball-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 8 Jun 2026 14:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59176</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kelly, Yehl Named NCBWA District 2 Co-Players of the Year</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-kelly-yehl-named-ncbwa-district-2-co-players-of-the-year</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-kelly-yehl-named-ncbwa-district-2-co-players-of-the-year</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/8/060626_BSB_CalPoly_NCAAT_GB_250_large.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Sophomore Gavin Kelly and redshirt junior Maxx Yehl have been named the District 2 Co-Players of the Year by the National Collegiate Baseball Writers Association.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/060626_BSB_CalPoly_NCAAT_GB_250_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/060626_BSB_CalPoly_NCAAT_GB_250_large.jpg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/060626_BSB_CalPoly_NCAAT_GB_250_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 8 Jun 2026 14:34:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59178</s:story_id></item><item><title>Three Mountaineers Set for NCAA Outdoor Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/10/track-field-three-mountaineers-set-for-ncaa-outdoor-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/10/track-field-three-mountaineers-set-for-ncaa-outdoor-championships</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Annishka McDonald competes in the high jump at the NCAA East First Round in Lexington, Kentucky" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/10/IMG_1742.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Three members of the West Virginia University track and field team are set to compete at the 2026 NCAA Outdoor Track and Field Championships, held at Hayward Field in Eugene, Oregon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/IMG_1742.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/IMG_1742.jpg"><media:title>Annishka McDonald competes in the high jump at the NCAA East First Round in Lexington, Kentucky</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/10/IMG_1742.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 11:59:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59181</s:story_id></item><item><title>Athletics To Retire Pat White’s No. 5</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/football-athletics-to-retire-pat-whites-no-5</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/football-athletics-to-retire-pat-whites-no-5</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="pat white 5" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker announced today that the department will retire football legend Pat White's No. 5 this fall at a home game to be determined later this summer.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg"><media:title>pat white 5</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 5 Jun 2026 10:27:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59167</s:story_id></item><item><title>Eleven CRCA Scholar-Athletes Match Program Record</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/9/rowing-eleven-crca-scholar-athletes-match-program-record</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/9/rowing-eleven-crca-scholar-athletes-match-program-record</guid><category>Rowing</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="A graphic recognizing the 11 rowers named to the CRCA Scholar Athlete team" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/9/ROW26_CRCAScholarAthleteTeam_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Eleven members of the West Virginia University rowing team were honored by the Collegiate Rowing Coaches Association as 2026 CRCA Scholar-Athletes, including eight with GPAs of 4.0.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/ROW26_CRCAScholarAthleteTeam_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/ROW26_CRCAScholarAthleteTeam_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>A graphic recognizing the 11 rowers named to the CRCA Scholar Athlete team</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/ROW26_CRCAScholarAthleteTeam_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 9 Jun 2026 12:11:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>12</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59179</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>